The published MonitoredInstance contract is
bind-existing and observe-only. Reconcile binds
by explicit instanceId or a unique
ListMonitoredInstances match on compartmentId
plus displayName, and it never invents create,
update, or delete operations.
Direct binds are explicit. The runtime
preflights GetMonitoredInstance when instanceId
is set so a missing direct bind does not fall
back to list adoption.
ListMonitoredInstances returns
MonitoredInstanceSummary rather than the full
body, so the runtime reruns GetMonitoredInstance
after a list bind to project timeCreated,
timeUpdated, and lifecycleDetails from the full
object.
Delete is CR-local unbind only. The controller
clears the finalizer immediately, never calls
auxiliary monitoring or workrequest helpers, and
treats observed DELETING or DELETED lifecycle as
terminating read state rather than managed
delete progress.
